   "source": [
    "# Physics-Informed Battery Degradation Models\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook will automatically clone the GitHub repository, install the necessary dependencies, and run the Symbolic Regression + PySINDy experiment. It will then display the final generated plots."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 1. Clone the repository\n",
    "!git clone https://github.com/sushxxnth/battery-degradation.git\n",
    "%cd battery-degradation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 2. Install dependencies\n",
    "!pip install gplearn pysindy scikit-learn seaborn matplotlib pandas numpy scipy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 3. Run the experiment\n",
    "!python3 battery_symbolic_sindy.py"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Visualizing the Results\n",
    "Once the script finishes (it takes about 10-15 minutes to run the Genetic Algorithms), it saves the plots to the `reports/` folder. We will display them below."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import IPython.display as display\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "reports_dir = 'reports'\n",
    "images = [\n",
    "    'soh_prediction_curves.png',\n",
    "    'parity_plot.png',\n",
    "    'metrics_comparison.png',\n",
    "    'rul_comparison.png',\n",
    "    'feature_correlation_heatmap.png',\n",
    "    'error_histograms.png'\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "for img in images:\n",
    "    img_path = os.path.join(reports_dir, img)\n",
    "    if os.path.exists(img_path):\n",
    "        print(f\"--- {img} ---\")\n",
    "        display.display(display.Image(filename=img_path))\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        print(f\"Image not found: {img}\")"
   ]
  }
